cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper deals with weakly-supervised semantic segmentation, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning architectures (cs.LG) and loss functions (cs.AI) to improve the segmentation results. Additionally, the paper uses datasets related to urban scenes (cs.MM) and autonomous navigation (cs.RO), which further support the likelihood of these sub-categories.
